    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, you're saying it's a \"small price to pay\"? I'm the one who has to pay it. If my margins are already thin, even a \"slight\" increase could mean I have to cut staff or raise prices so much that customers stop coming. Don't you think there's a risk that this actually hurts the very people it's supposed to help by making it harder for local shops to stay open?",
